17
{
  name { Second Floor Landing  }
  desc {
"   This landing has a mosaic laid out on the floor made of tiny pieces of
tile.  The intricate pieces are fitted so precisely that it looks like
there was no grout used.  Workmanship of this quality is almost unheard of,
and the cost must have been extraordinary.  As you make your way to your
exit, you see that the image shifts, showing a man fighting off dark
creatures.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { n, 19 }
	to { e, 18 }
	to { d, 16 }
  }
}

18
{
  name { The Storage Closet  }
  desc {
"   There are boxes and racks everywhere to hold many different types of
weapons and junk.  The racks are all empty and the boxes hold nothing of
value.  No one has been here in some time, judging from the dust that
covers every surface in here.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { w, 17 }
  }
}

19
{
  name { The Ready Room  }
  desc {
"   This room has mannequins set at equal intervals along the walls with
matching lockers that permit warriors to store their equipment for ease of
access at a moments notice.  This spartan set up is elegant in its 
simplicity.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { n, 20 }
	to { s, 17 }
  }
}

20
{
  name { The Infirmary  }
  desc {
"   Cots, separated by sheets, are laid out geometrically throughout the
room.  One cot still has some old bandages caked with blood so old as to be
black laid off to the side.  A table, covered with similarly old blood is
in the center of the room with some saws, scalpels and other rudimentary
surgical tools.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { e, 21 }
	to { s, 19 }
  }
}

21
{
  name { The Archers' Hall  }
  desc {
"   This long hallway dominates the northern facing of the tower.  The north
facing edge has some murder holes in them to allow defenders to pour
boiling oil onto attackers attempting to breach the gate below.  There is
an abundance of archers slits in the wall as well, allowing up to twenty
men to fire arrows on an advancing enemy.  The fire pits and cauldrons
caked with sludge are silent and cold now.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { e, 22 }
	to { w, 20 }
  }
}

22
{
  name { The Hangout  }
  desc {
"   This small room has a makeshift still in one corner, disappointingly
empty.  There are some trestle tables and a variety of makeshift stools
scattered every which way.  The room is further cluttered by a variety of
gambling artifacts.  Dice, playing cards, and a dartboard leaning against
the wall makes this look like an inn after a major brawl.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { s, 23 }
	to { w, 21 }
  }
}

23
{
  name { The Training Salle  }
  desc {
"   This room is plainly furnished, with a large mats laid on the floor.
There are also boxes and grids laid out on the floor that are worn with
age and countless feet.  Along the wall, there are many practice weapons,
either made of wood or with their edges blunted.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { n, 22 }
	to { s, 24 }
  }
}

24
{
  name { The Cat's Nest  }
  desc {
"   This room is well appointed, with tapestries and rugs to soften the feel
of it.  The effect is marred, however, by the bunches of animal hair and
sickly ammonia smell of animal droppings and urine.  The sound of furtive
movement reaches your ears.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { n, 23 }
	to { northwest, 25 }
  }
}

25
{
  name { Bottom of the Stairs  }
  desc {
"   There are narrow slits in the outer wall of this staircase that allows
fresh air to come into this section of the tower.  Not much can be seen
outside, but the light coming in allows you to see the rough precision that
went into building this tower.
  }
  flags { no_sum, private }
  exits {
	to { u, 26 }
	to { southeast, 24 }
  }
}

